---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import aboutMeImage from "../assets/about_me.jpg";
---

<div class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] backdrop-blur-sm p-6 sm:p-10 shadow-2xl">
  <Image
    src={aboutMeImage}
    width={1200}
    alt="Pablo García Ruiz"
    format="webp"
    class="w-full aspect-video object-cover rounded-2xl border border-white/10 shadow-xl"
  />

  <div class="mt-8">
    <p class="mt-5 text-sm sm:text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
      So, Computer Vision Engineer, you already know that part,
      <em>you're literally on my portfolio</em>. What the projects don't really
      show is that I'm a bit of a restless creative underneath it all. Give me
      a hard problem and I'll happily disappear into it for a weekend, whether
      that's a <span class="text-[#ff004f] font-medium">CV paper, a scrappy web app, or some side
      project</span> I convinced myself I needed to build. My mum has a word
      for it: <strong class="text-[#ff004f]">"de culo inquieto"</strong>,
      roughly, someone who can't sit still and is always chasing the next
      thing to make, learn, or take apart.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-6 border-l-2 border-[#ff004f]/60 pl-4 text-sm sm:text-base text-white/60 italic leading-relaxed">
  Fair warning: I collect hobbies like other people collect stamps. Right now that's painting, graphic design, cooking things that probably shouldn't work, and tattooing. Ask me again in six months, the list will have grown.
</p>
  </div>
</div>